{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"6266","heading":"Notification of nuclear criticality and non-nuclear incidents","label":"6266 Notification of nuclear criticality and non-nuclear incidents","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/stA/ptVI/sptB/ch606/schIII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Prior ProvisionsProvisions similar to those in this section were contained in , War and National Defense, prior to repeal by .section 2736 of Title 50Pub. L. 119–60, § 3111(b)(1)","Amendments2025—, realigned margins.Pub. L. 119–60, § 3111(d)(2)(B)"],"amendments":["Amendments2025—, realigned margins.Pub. L. 119–60, § 3111(d)(2)(B)"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—Notification","label":"a .—Notification","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary of Energy or the Administrator, as the case may be, shall submit to the appropriate congressional committees a notification of a nuclear criticality incident resulting from a covered program that results in an injury or fatality or results in the shutdown, or partial shutdown, of a covered facility by not later than 15 days after the date of such incident.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Elements of Notification","label":"b .—Elements of Notification","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A description of the incident, including the cause of the incident.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In the case of a criticality incident, whether the incident caused a facility, or part of a facility, to be shut down.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The effect, if any, on the mission of the Administration or the Office of Environmental Management of the Department of Energy.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Any corrective action taken in response to the incident.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":".—Database","label":"c .—Database","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall maintain a record of incidents described in paragraph (2).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/c/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fc%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A nuclear criticality incident that results in an injury or fatality or results in the shutdown, or partial shutdown, of a covered facility.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/c/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fc%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A non-nuclear incident that results in serious bodily injury or fatality at a covered facility.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":".—Cooperation","label":"d .—Cooperation","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In carrying out this section, the Secretary and the Administrator shall ensure that each management and operating contractor of a covered facility cooperates in a timely manner.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":".—Definitions","label":"e .—Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/e/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fe%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/e/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/e/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fe%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the congressional defense committees; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/e/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/e/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fe%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Committee on Energy and Commerce of the House of Representatives and the Committee on Energy and Natural Resources of the Senate.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/e/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fe%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/e/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/e/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fe%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a facility of the nuclear security enterprise; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/e/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/e/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fe%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a facility conducting activities for the defense environmental cleanup program of the Office of Environmental Management of the Department of Energy.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/e/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fe%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/e/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/e/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fe%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"programs of the Administration; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/e/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6266/e/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6266%2Fe%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"defense environmental cleanup programs of the Office of Environmental Management of the Department of Energy.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]}
